serviceObjectGroupId.description: Service Object Group that the Service Object is being added to/removed from.

serviceObjectId.description: Service Object that is being added or removed from group membership.

networkObjectGroupId.description: Network Object Group that the Network Object is being added to/removed from.

networkObjectId.description: Network Object that is being added or removed from group membership.

policyControlEnforced.description: Default True, Security rules (contracts) will be enforced.

policyControlEnforcementIngress.description: Default True, If this is set to False, policy is enforced on egress traffic. If this is set to True, policy is enforced on ingress traffic.

gatewayIp.description: The IP address and mask of the default gateway.

treatAsVirtualIpAddress.description: Indicates whether the subnet is a virtual IP address configured for the associated bridge domain.

primaryIpAddress.description:
Indicates if the subnet is preferred (primary) over the available alternatives. Only one preferred subnet is allowed.
      Affects DHCP Relay only.

advertisedExternally.description: The subnet can be exported to a routed connection.

preferred.description: The subnet is preferred over other subnets associated to its parent BD.

sharedBetweenVrfs.description: The subnet can be shared with and exported to multiple contexts (VRFs) in the same tenant or across tenants as part of a shared service.

ipDataPlaneLearning.description: Choose whether to enable or disable IP address learning for this subnet.

etherType.description: The EtherType of the filter entry.

arpFlag.description: The Address Resolution Protocol flag for a filter entry. The filter entry is a combination of network traffic classification properties.

ipProtocol.description: The IP protocol for a filter entry. The filter entry is a combination of network traffic classification properties.

matchOnlyFragments.description: Match only packet fragments. When enabled, the rule applies to any IP fragment with an offset that is greater than 0 (all IP fragments except the first). When disabled, the rule will not apply to IP fragments with an offset greater than 0 because TCP/UDP port information can only be checked in initial fragments.

applyBothDirections.description: Sets the contract filter to apply on both ingress and egress traffic directions.

reverseFilterPorts.description: Enables the filter to apply on both ingress and egress traffic.

globalAlias.description: The scope of a contract between two or more EPGs.

intraEpgIsolation.description: Intra-EPG endpoint isolation policies provide full isolation for virtual or physical endpoints; no communication is allowed between endpoints in an EPG that is operating with isolation enforced.

bdMacAddress.description: Bridge Domain MAC address, default: null.

limitLocalIpLearning.description: Limit Local IP Learning to BD/EPG Subnets, default: true.

epMoveDetectionModeGarp.description: GARP-based endpoint move detection, default: false.
